Synaxis Frequently Asked Questions
───────────────────────────────────

Q1) How do I set up Synaxis?
A1) Read INSTALL. Short version:
    autoreconf -fi && ./configure --prefix=$HOME/services \
      --enable-modules=... && make && make install

Q2) How do I connect Synaxis to Cathexis?
A2) Add a Connect block in Cathexis ircd.conf pointing to
    Synaxis, and set matching address/port/password in
    $HOME/services/etc/x3.conf under "uplinks".

Q3) Can I use TLS for the S2S link?
A3) Yes. Set "ssl" "1" in the uplinks block of x3.conf.
    Optionally configure ssl_certfile, ssl_keyfile, ssl_cafile,
    and ssl_fingerprint for mutual TLS and cert pinning.

Q4) I get "You must first authenticate with NickServ"
A4) Register: /msg NickServ REGISTER <account> <password>
    Login:    /msg NickServ AUTH <account> <password>
    Or:       /msg NickServ IDENTIFY <account> <password>

Q5) How do I add new command bindings after upgrading?
A5) /msg OpServ REBINDALL

Q6) What services are available?
A6) NickServ (58 commands), ChanServ (90 commands),
    OpServ (143 commands), MemoServ (17 commands),
    HostServ (14 commands), BotServ (23 commands),
    HelpServ, SpamServ, Global, WebTV.

Q7) What channel modes does Synaxis support?
A7) Full Cathexis prefix modes:
    +q (~) Owner, +a (&) Protect, +o (@) Op,
    +h (%) Halfop, +v (+) Voice.

Q8) What password hashing does Synaxis use?
A8) Argon2id (OWASP 2024 parameters). Legacy MD5 passwords
    are auto-migrated on first login.
